comments[14]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:59:02.798Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: existing validate,deps visualization,and one-time living-map audits do not provide schema-aware graph coverage profiles and remediation plans; this extends canonical governance rather than replacing those items."
  "2026-07-17T13:10:36.159Z",codex-root,"Implementation progress: added a counts-first relationship governance report covering active and terminal dangling references, retired sentinels, ordering-only cycles, stale lifecycle blocks, isolates, sparse nodes, deterministic samples, explicit exemptions, cancellation, and safe remediation text; validation now reuses shared assembly."
  "2026-07-17T13:47:20.393Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: linked governance suite passed; full repository coverage passed 5,798 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; lint/static/security/package gates passed. Fresh packed SDK audit and CLI temp project proved dependency/lifecycle blocked parity, graph assembly, semantic traversal, bounded path evidence, and zero history drift. This tranche is complete; broader type/profile baselines, change-since-baseline, cursors, executable dry-run plans, and all audit-surface integration remain canonical open scope."
  "2026-07-17T14:12:23.856Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 5843a507-bc02-480c-b73f-b95c37e34b46: trimmed/custom governance assemblies now treat missing predecessor detail conservatively as unknown/open instead of falsely reporting a stale lifecycle block. Regression coverage and full exact coverage pass."
  "2026-07-17T15:21:09.861Z",codex-root,"PR #579 review round 1: integrity findings now repartition dangling references with the audit invocation's custom terminal predicate rather than assembly-time defaults. A custom terminal holder regression proves missing_reference_terminal versus missing_reference_active classification. Full 5,800-test coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-17T16:10:55.038Z",codex-sdk-graph,"PR #579 review round 2 evidence: ordering-cycle governance now reports registered allowSelf ordering loops as one-member cycles, and malformed non-string isolate exemptions are ignored safely. Regression proof composes custom registry assembly with self-cycle governance. Full repository coverage passes 298 files / 5,802 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; typecheck, ESLint, zero-clone, 100% docstring, package-boundary, and token-budget gates pass."
  "2026-07-17T19:21:58.364Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress: the governance audit engine is now operable from the workspace surface via pm graph audit (CLI + pm_graph MCP + PmClient.graph). Counts-first envelope reports finding_count, findings_by_severity, findings_by_code (subject-count weighted), and the structural coverage profile; --sample bounds per-finding evidence, --exempt-isolate (repeatable/comma-separated) suppresses policy findings for deliberate isolates, --summary drops rows. Regression spec covers missing_reference_active + isolated_active_node detection, severity rollup consistency, and exemption behavior on a live temp workspace."
  "2026-07-17T23:52:43.357Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress (graph-platform lane 2026-07-18): both recorded audit-scope gaps closed — (1) ordering_cycle now gates severity on lifecycle: cycles confined to terminal members downgrade to info legacy_ordering_cycle with changelog-safe remediation text, error reserved for cycles touching >=1 active item (2ler/demq legacy-split precedent applied as recorded in note 3); (2) new duplicate_edge / legacy_duplicate_edge info findings catch parallel same-family spellings including reciprocal blocked_by/blocks pairs, oriented via the shared analytics helpers (isTransitiveKind/orientTransitiveEdge/transitiveFamilyKey now exported — single implementation, no clones), endpoint-lifecycle gated per note 4. Additionally the first remediation-plan surface shipped: pm graph plan (12th subcommand, CLI+MCP+SDK) derives exact dry-run remove/retype/supersede/waive/investigate proposals with policy code, evidence, rationale, and confidence from audit findings plus redundancy witness rows — never auto-applied, never invents an edge. Verified live in a temp workspace: active cycle=error, terminal pair=legacy info, reciprocal pair=duplicate_edge."
  "2026-07-18T01:35:49.248Z",codex-root,"PR #581 Greptile P1 follow-up: accepted review comment 3607265146. runGraphPlan now passes the public --limit bound into redundancyLimit, so callers raising the output limit above the planner's 25-row default receive all discoverable redundant-edge remediation proposals instead of a prematurely truncated plan. Regression builds a 28-node graph with 26 witnessed shortcuts and proves limit=100 returns every step without truncation; focused graph suite passes 21/21."
  "2026-07-20T03:30:17.177Z",maintainer-agent,"Continuation scope 2026-07-20: finish raw duplicate dependency-row integrity findings, per-type isolate policy, signed change-since-baseline reporting, remediation integration, and docs/tests. Existing OSSF code-scanning alerts 17-23 map to canonical pm-003j/pm-0yi7/pm-2d7k/pm-obq2/pm-rrt1; GH-595/584/582 map to pm-wrss/pm-zt1c/pm-zwya, so no duplicates were created or claimed."
  "2026-07-20T03:54:53.713Z",maintainer-agent,"Pre-push Greptile review 801a7677-68c3-4ee6-983a-2b42b8c1bb75: accepted the P1 malformed-baseline finding. decodeBaseline now rejects null affected_subjects_by_code/profile fields, with regressions proving defective persisted census files are ignored instead of crashing later graph audits."
  "2026-07-20T04:04:18.320Z",maintainer-agent,"Review evidence: exact-head Greptile review 84ef563e-f412-44be-80e5-462936a5134d completed at confidence 5/5 with no actionable findings. It specifically confirmed defensive baseline decoding, fresh baseline delta evaluation outside caches, corrected finding/subject census semantics, and contract parity."
  "2026-07-20T04:17:12.972Z",maintainer-agent,"Final branch evidence before PR: all 4 linked governance/remediation tests passed; full repository coverage is exact 100/100/100/100 across 5,993 tests. Repo audit produced no warning/error findings (12 informational categories only), while temp installed-package baseline proof reported signed +1 node/+1 active/+1 isolate drift after mutation and a durable cache hit on the next process. ESLint, zero-clone jscpd, 100% docstrings, package boundary, token budget, contracts, docs/skills, secret scan, and 88-command package-first dogfood gates passed. Latest pm-changelog 2026.7.18 check reports CHANGELOG.md unchanged."
  "2026-07-20T04:53:50.464Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #622 review round 1: accepted Greptile's plan exemption P1, CodeRabbit's neutral rebuild key, and Gemini's persisted-baseline hardening/determinism findings. Plan now honors isolate-exempt types; malformed count/profile baselines are rejected; all bot comments/reviews were voted, answered, and 12 inline threads resolved. Final review-fix coverage: 5,994 tests at exact 100/100/100/100."
notes[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T17:08:32.150Z",maintainer-agent,"Manual relationship-density baseline (2026-07-14 pass #82) — the measurement this audit feature should automate. Method: dump .item.dependencies for every ACTIVE item + parent links; degree counts both endpoints; closed-item out-edges not counted (active-graph view). Before enrichment: 211 active items, 269 dep edges + 210 parent edges, 95 items with zero out-edges, 67 items with total degree <= 1 (parent-only). After a 67-edge related-kind enrichment batch: degree<=1 = 3 (pm-7zs0 reminder, pm-x2vx, pm-p5u6 — deliberate; no honest semantic partner). Enrichment structure worth encoding as audit heuristics: (1) scanner-finding clusters get a 2-level hub topology — members -> file-cluster representative -> rule-class representative (Semgrep non-literal-RegExp 30 items across 6 files; prototype-pollution 3; spawn-shell-true 4; dependabot-cooldown 2 under pm-oz8u); (2) story -> implementing-task edges (pm-6ixn -> pm-oz8u); (3) cross-epic complementarity edges documented in bodies but absent as edges (pm-n7rr <-> pm-usfg/pm-pbyu/pm-mpbb); (4) class-sibling edges from defect-family ledgers. Audit check candidates: degree<=1 ratio on active items, container out-degree zero, documented-in-body-but-unlinked pairs."
  "2026-07-17T20:01:08.970Z",maintainer-agent,"Remediation-surface addition via the graph-query-surface lane (2026-07-17): pm graph redundancy is the transitive-reduction detector this audit's stale/redundant-link remediation plans can consume — each finding carries the stored edge in its original spelling plus a semantic-orientation witness path, so remediation can propose removing shortcut edges with evidence. Live workspace scan found real blocked_by/blocks shortcut edges (bounded scan, truncated at --limit). Governance audit itself unchanged; redundancy stays a separate opt-in projection because shortcut edges are sometimes deliberate emphasis."
  "2026-07-17T21:40:24.082Z",maintainer-agent,"Scope finding (2026-07-17 review, dogfooding pm graph audit): the audit reports 8 error-severity ordering_cycle findings spanning 49 items — ALL 49 verified terminal (closed/canceled legacy; e.g. pm-06t/pm-2xl Milestone-0 era, pm-0c0g/pm-8kxm, pm-0pvk/pm-s9hl pairs). validate lifecycle stays ok because it gates active holders. The graph audit needs the same legacy/active severity split validate's checks gained (pm-2ler dangling-refs precedent, pm-demq unknown-authors precedent): terminal-only cycles should downgrade to info with a legacy_* counter, error reserved for cycles touching >=1 active item. Never repair the closed items themselves (changelog drag). legacy_no_blocker_sentinel:98 + missing_reference_terminal:3 are the already-registered legacy sets (2ler ghosts) — audit correctly labels those legacy_/terminal already; ordering_cycle is the one code missing the split."
  "2026-07-17T21:42:07.808Z",maintainer-agent,"Second audit-scope gap (2026-07-17 review, code-read of sdk/graph): exact-duplicate stored edges are invisible to BOTH shipped surfaces. findRedundantRelationshipEdges orients blocked_by/blocks into one semantic family but its witness BFS skips the direct edge at depth 0 (analytics.ts expandWitnessFrontier), so a reciprocal stored pair (A blocked_by B AND B blocks A) or any parallel same-orientation edge yields no witness and is never reported — correct for transitive REDUCTION semantics, but nothing else catches the duplicate either: governance.ts audit codes are exactly {missing_reference_terminal, legacy_no_blocker_sentinel, ordering_cycle, stale_lifecycle_block, isolated_active_node, sparse_active_node} — no duplicate_edge code. Extension direction: add an info-severity duplicate_edge audit finding (same-family same-orientation parallel edges, reciprocal inverse spellings included), active-holders gated per the legacy-split policy in the previous note. Analytics semantics stay unchanged."
  "2026-07-17T22:44:10.891Z",maintainer-agent,"Census-method transition (2026-07-18 pass #98): the manual grep/dump density census from note 1 is now automated natively — `pm graph audit --summary` profile is the canonical baseline source going forward. Baseline 2026-07-18: nodes 1859, edges 3073 (parent 1681 / related 918 / blocked_by 353 / blocks 69 / discovered_from 36 / child 15 / incident_from 1), active_nodes 225, isolated_active_nodes 0, degree_leq_one_active_nodes 2 (deliberate pm-p5u6/pm-x2vx pair), missing_nodes 3 (known terminal ghosts). Historic grep-census figures (3,051 #92 / 3,091 #95 / 3,096 #97) used the manual method — the ~23-edge delta vs the native profile is method difference (declared-row grep vs registry graph), not edge loss; never reconcile the two series row-for-row."
  "2026-07-17T23:53:02.107Z",maintainer-agent,"Remaining canonical scope after the 2026-07-18 tranche (audit codes + pm graph plan): (1) coverage profiles varying by item type/lifecycle/age/role (today one policy with exempt-isolate escape hatch); (2) explicit attributable waiver records (plan proposes waive ops but nothing persists them); (3) resumable remediation workflows + changelog-safe closed-item batch tooling (plan is dry-run only by design); (4) reuse of the finding contract across health/validate/stats/aggregate/package-audit surfaces (today pm graph audit/plan only); (5) temporal findings (stale inferred relationships, snapshot drift). Baseline census impact: the 8 legacy-era ordering_cycle errors recorded in note 3 now report as info legacy_ordering_cycle — expect findings_by_severity.error to drop accordingly on the next native census; the duplicate_edge counters are new columns, not comparable to any prior series."
  "2026-07-18T00:15:37.216Z",maintainer-agent,"PR#581 Greptile P1 disposition (2026-07-18): raw identical stored dependency rows (same holder, same kind, same target twice) are canonicalized away by RelationshipGraph edge-identity dedup BEFORE the graph audit runs, so duplicate_edge deliberately covers only cross-spelling parallels that survive canonicalization. Detecting raw same-row duplicates = the \"duplicate canonical identity\" integrity-family AC of this item and must scan pre-assembly item rows (validate/storage layer), not the assembled graph. Do not re-file — extend the integrity family here when that check is built."
  "2026-07-18T05:40:00.985Z",maintainer-agent,"PR#581 MERGED 2026-07-18: shipped from this item — lifecycle severity split (legacy_ordering_cycle informational vs active ordering_cycle error), duplicate_edge/legacy_duplicate_edge cross-spelling detection (shared orientation logic with analytics), and pm graph plan (12th subcommand) dry-run remediation with remove/retype/supersede/waive/investigate steps carrying policy code + evidence + confidence. Honest AC remainder: (a) raw same-row duplicate-identity integrity family at the pre-assembly storage layer (note 7 disposition — canonicalization hides these from the assembled graph); (b) coverage profiles by item type/lifecycle/age/role with explicit valid-isolate policy; (c) change-since-baseline deltas in reports; (d) health/validate/stats/aggregate/package-audit reusing the ONE SDK policy+finding contract; (e) changelog-safe closed-item remediation batches."
